Independent and peaceful reunification of Korea supported 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; New Delhi, June 8 (KCNA) -- A meeting commemorating the first anniversary of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration was held at the Indian Institute of Socialist Education on June 4 under the co-sponsorship of the All India Indo-Korean Friendship Association and the Indian Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification.
 At the meeting the reporter and speakers said that the declaration is a landmark for Korea's reunification provided thanks to the patriotic idea and courageous decision of leader Kim Jong Il and that Korea should be reunified peacefully at an early date according to the declaration.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Anti-reunification elements of South Korea are tightening the political and military ties with foreign forces against the DPRK, which is in contravention of the spirit of the declaration and a deliberate move to bring north-south relations back to those of confrontation in the past, they noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should stop the moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK and withdraw its troops and nuclear weapons from South Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Indian people will extend full support and solidarity to the Korean people in their struggle to reunify the country on the principle of national independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A solidarity message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting.

Remark of president of Grand National Party assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- The spokesman for the National Democratic Front of South Korea released a statement on June 6 denouncing Ri Hoe Chang, president of the Grand National Party, and his henchmen for their remarks chilling the desire of the compatriots for reunification and inciting confrontation with the DPRK recently, according to Seoul-based Voice of National Salvation.
 Recalling that not content with echoing the Bush administration's talk about "reciprocity" and "transparency," Ri Hoe Chang, some days ago, did not bother to let loose outcries pulling up the DPRK over the tour of Mt. Kumgang and its "human rights issue" and describing the north as their "principal enemy," the spokesman accused his party heavyweights of opposing the "June 15 Grand Seminar on National Reunification." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He termed Ri Hoe Chang's such act of blocking the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration, indifferent to the country, the nation and the reunification, an unpardonable anti-national move as it challenges the desire and aspiration of the nation for reconciliation and unity and a despicable pro-U.S. flunkeyist and traitorous act of meekly following the U.S. hardline policy to stifle the DPRK in utter disregard of the interests of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such traitors and stumbling blocks lying in the way of reunification as Ri Hoe Chang should be immediately eliminated today when there is a bright prospect of national reunification, the spokesman said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Hoe Chang should stop behaving indiscreetly, well aware of the will of the people for the independent reunification of the nation in the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our people will decisively smash the splittist moves of a handful of anti-reunification traitors such as Ri Hoe Chang and join hands with the compatriots in the north in the efforts to achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country as early as possible and build a strong and prosperous nation on this land without fail.

Anniversary of June 10 anti-Japanese demonstration observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today dedicates a signed article to the 75th anniversary of the June 10 anti-Japanese demonstration.
 The June 10 anti-Japanese demonstration was a just resistance of the Korean people against the Japanese imperialists' colonial rule and a mass anti-Japanese patriotic struggle to retake the usurped country and national sovereignty. 
 Noting that the aspiration of the June 10 anti-Japanese demonstrators has not yet been realized on a nation-wide scale, the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists' domination and interference are a main obstacle to the independent and peaceful reunification of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists have escalated political and military confrontation and tensions between the north and the south, invariably pursuing a policy of confrontation and war against the DPRK for over half a century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-reunification forces and military warmongers of South Korea are blatantly challenging the cause of independent national reunification, favouring the U.S. imperialists' policy to stifle the DPRK in collusion with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are whetting their swords to stage a comeback to Korea, pursuant to the U.S. imperialists' hostile policy towards the DPRK and keeping pace with their moves to provoke a new war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people, who have witnessed the start of the new history of independent national reunification, will never allow the U.S. imperialists and the Japanese reactionaries to trample down the dignity and sovereignty of the Korean nation and block national reunification. 
 National independence serves as a pro-reunification patriotic banner which can never be bartered for anything in the light of either the present political situation or tasks before the Korean people. National reunification can be achieved only through a vigorous struggle against outside forces and for independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to protect national dignity and sovereignty and realize national reunification in conformity with the will and interests of the nation it is necessary to reject flunkeyism and dependence on foreign forces and resolutely struggle against foreign forces' aggression and interference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The whole Korean nation should continue to make a dynamic advance for independent national reunification in the spirit of the June 15 joint declaration.

U.S. urged to change its attitude 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- The Bush administration is strongly denounced at home and abroad for recklessly pushing forward the establishment of "Missile Defence" system (MD).
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is attributable to high-handed and arbitrary practices the Bush administration has perpetrated while persistently pursuing an isolationist and conservative policy after failing to face up to the trend of the times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Independence, peace and friendship have become a mainstream of the times and the 21st century will be a century of peace and cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the hope of the world people to achieve independent progress and prosperity in the new century, helping and cooperating with each other in a peaceful environment free from aggression and war. The leftovers of the old era such as isolationist and conservative policy and high-handed and arbitrary practices can no longer go down with anyone in the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush administration is well advised to behave itself,  properly understanding the changed times and the aspiration and demand of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no need to say that the U.S. will stand more strongly protested and denounced and thoroughly isolated at home and abroad in the future if it continues behaving as now. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is well advised to draw a lesson from this and change its attitude.
